## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

For loaded files, the same style object is used in multiple cells.

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

Please, see https://github.com/frosas/exceljs-style-bug-scenario for the full setup.

Copying the meaty parts here for context:

```javascript
const workbook = new Excel.Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.readFile("spreadsheet.xlsx");
const seenStyles = new Set();
workbook.eachSheet((sheet) => {
  sheet.eachRow((row) => {
    row.eachCell((cell) => {
      if (seenStyles.has(cell.style)) {
        console.log(
          `${cell.$col$row} style object was already seen on another cell`
        );
      }
      seenStyles.add(cell.style);
    });
  });
});
```

The above prints 

```
$B$1 style object was already seen on another cell
$A$2 style object was already seen on another cell
$B$2 style object was already seen on another cell
```

for a 2x2 spreadsheet.

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

No "style object was already seen on another cell" lines are printed.

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

This is the workaround I'm currently applying:

```ts
import cloneDeep from 'lodash/cloneDeep'

/** Fixes multiple cells possibly referring to the same style object */
function fixCellStyle(cell: Cell) {
  cell.style = cloneDeep(cell.style)
}
```

